text: Adams County is a county found in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, 29,538 people lived there. The county seat is Natchez. The county was created on April 2, 1799. It is named for John Adams, the second President of the United States. == References == Category:1799 establishments in the United States Category:18th-century establishments in Mississippi Territory
title: Adams County, Mississippi
